            "title": "New methods for the ab-initio simulation of correlated systems",
            "abstract": "Strong electronic correlations are at the heart of many interesting phenomena. For the theoretical description of these materials, a proper treatment of the local atomic physics is required. We propose a novel approach combining functionals of the electron density and functionals of the one-particle reduced density matrix to improve this description. The proposed method has a solid foundation in reduced density-matrix functional theory and no double-counting problem arises. It employs a decomposition of the electron-electron interaction in real space. The interaction close to the correlated...",
